- (F, s) âˆ’â†’ (F , s ) (Action transition)
where F is a frame, s is a state, deï¬ned as a tuple (v,Ï) with v : Var â†’ Z (variable values), and Ï captures the
global resource state. As we are dealing with a distributed system, we assume that each object manages its own

